16. Tribunus] Seil. militum. There were six of these to each legion. In early times they commanded the legion successively day by day, and even at this period a tribune might still be called by courtesy‚ the commander of a legion. Horace, at the age of 22, joined the army of M. Brutus in Greece, and was appointed a tribunus. He says of himself x Quod mihi pareret legio Romana tribuno. It is impossible th'at so young and obscure a man could have been actual commander of a legion.

17. Praefectus] The eommander of the auxiliary horse, appointed by the imperator from among his Roman officere.

18. regatus] The consul's or imperator’s lieutenant, generally in command of a detaehment.

19. Praetor] i. q. imperator. Qui praeit exercitui. 20. Plerosque ipsos] ‘⁶ Most of them personally.”
